articles.title: Windsurf’s CEO goes to Google; OpenAI’s acquisition falls apart - TechCrunch
articles.description: Notably, Google is not taking a stake in Windsurf and will not have any control over the company.
articles.content:
OpenAI’s deal to acquire the viral AI coding startup Windsurf for $3 billion fell apart on Friday, according to The Verge.
In a shocking twist, Google DeepMind is now hiring Windsurf CEO Varun Mohan… [+3756 chars]
